	<a name="footnote26-23905_000_004">26.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/js-h/1.15-20?lang=eng#14" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">JS&mdash;H 1:15&ndash;20</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote27-23905_000_004">27.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/89.title?lang=eng" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 89</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote28-23905_000_004">28.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See Official Declaration 2.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote29-23905_000_004">29.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <span class="emphasis">Church News,</span> 1 Aug. 1998, 3, 12; 13 Mar. 1999, 9; 4 Mar. 2000, 7; 24 June 2000, 9.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote30-23905_000_004">30.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Even the Son of God endured such an experience, &ldquo;saying, Father, if thou be willing, remove this cup from me: nevertheless not my will, but thine, be done&rdquo; (<a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/luke/22.42?lang=eng#41" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Luke 22:42</a>). The Father and the Son both knew what had to be done.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote31-23905_000_004">31.</a>
      </span>
				<p>Regarding obedience to divine law, see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/pgp/abr/3.25?lang=eng#24" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Abr. 3:25</a>. Regarding obedience to wise counsel from loving parents, see <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/eph/6.1?lang=eng#0" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Eph. 6:1</a>; <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/nt/col/3.20?lang=eng#19" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Col. 3:20</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote32-23905_000_004">32.</a>
      </span>
				<p>See <a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/bofm/hel/10.4-5?lang=eng#3" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">Hel. 10:4&ndash;5</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote33-23905_000_004">33.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/122.7?lang=eng#6" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 122:7</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote34-23905_000_004">34.</a>
      </span>
				<p><a href="http://lds.org/scriptures/dc-testament/dc/25.12?lang=eng#11" onclick="newWindow(this.href); return false;">D&amp;C 25:12</a>.</p>
			</li>
			<li class="footnote " id="-23905_000_004"><a name="-23905_000_004">&nbsp;</a>
				<span class="label">
	<a name="footnote35-23905_000_004">35.</a>
      </span>
				<p><span class="emphasis">Hymns,</span> no. 337; music composed by Joseph Parry; tune: SWANSEA.</p>
			</li>
		</ol>
                                        
